3.1.2 Lowering
Once the AST has been built, it must be lowered into the compiler’s IR. Lowering consists of two stages: lowering type declarations to build a type session (src/middle/lowering/ty_ctx.rs) and lowering function declarations to build IR function deﬁnitions (src/middle/lowering/ctx.rs). The type session carries information about the structures of types and is essential throughout type-checking, analysis and code generation. Its underlying data-structure (src/ty.rs) takes care to structurally unique function types and the u64 type, while handling record and sum-types nominally.
