3.2 Analysis Framework
Once the core pipeline was complete, I began working on the pipeline extensions implementing ASAP. As ASAP relies on not one but three data-ﬂow properties, I chose to implement a reusable framework within which each of the analyses could be implemented. This had another important beneﬁt. As the results from ASAP’s analyses are often extremely complex, testing them directly was impractical. However, by implementing a simpler analysis within the framework, the bulk of the analysis code could be tested without needing to verify results from ASAP’s analyses.
