3.4 Implementing Paths

Paths are, as mentioned, regular expressions extended to support the subsumption operator . This gives the impression that an eﬃcient treatment of paths would be to compile them into regular expressions and use an oﬀ-the-shelf regular expression library to implement operations over them. The problem with this approach becomes apparent when considering the role paths play in Proust’s data-ﬂow analyses.
